==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lucuma
<hw>Lu*cu"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>An American genus of sapotaceous trees bearing sweet and edible
fruits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <spn>Lucuma mammosum</spn> is called <xex>natural
marmalade</xex> in the West Indies; <spn>Lucuma Caimito</spn>, of Peru,
furnishes a delicious fruit called <prod>lucuma</prod> and
<prod>caimito</prod>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luddite</ent>⟦br⟧
